Vice President Biden hosted a meeting with leaders from the American and international nuclear industry to discuss adopting higher nuclear security standards. The meeting took place one day after the President's Nuclear Security Summit. The Vice President urged industry leaders to help achieve the President's goal of securing all vulnerable nuclear materials within four years. He emphasized the importance of a public-private partnership in ensuring global safety from nuclear threats. The Vice President also called on the industry to develop a set of best practices to be presented at the Nuclear Security Summit in South Korea in 2012.